Object.Field: select case when A1.cnt_a=B1.cnt_b then 1 else 0 end from ( select sum(count(etl_date)) cnt_a from dba_dependencies a, ldm.ods_etl_interface b where name='<?=odiRef.getLoadPlanStepInstance("STEP_NAME") ?>' and referenced_name <> '<?=odiRef.getLoadPlanStepInstance("STEP_NAME") ?>' and referenced_type='MATERIALIZED VIEW' and a.referenced_name=b.object_name and b.load_plan='<?=odiRef.getLoadPlanInstance("LOAD_PLAN_NAME") ?>' and etl_date=to_date(to_char(sysdate,'mm-dd-yy'),'mm-dd-yy')-1 group by a.referenced_name,etl_date ) A1,( select count(referenced_name) cnt_b from dba_dependencies where name='<?=odiRef.getLoadPlanStepInstance("STEP_NAME") ?>' and referenced_name <> '<?=odiRef.getLoadPlanStepInstance("STEP_NAME") ?>' and referenced_type='MATERIALIZED VIEW' ) B1

This is a static variable which is created to determine the FRESH RUN or RERUN of ODI Load Plan.
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM OGGS.ODI_CHECKS_GG WHERE ODI_FLAG = 'N' AND REPLICAT_NAME = '<?=snpRef.getLoadPlanInstance("LOAD_PLAN_NAME") ?>' AND TECHNOLOGY = 'ODI' AND STAGE='STG1'

This Variable is created to check load plan execution, weather it is executed for the day or not. It checks flag into ODI_CHECKS_GG table to determine the fresh execution of the load plans or user executed by mistakenly. If load plans are executing freshly then their flag should be 'N' if not then its successfully executed for the day. And if user executed load plan again by mistakenly then load plan is not getting executed as flag gets updated 'Y' after successful execution.
Below is the code inside:
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM OGGS.ODI_CHECKS_GG WHERE ODI_FLAG = 'N' AND REPLICAT_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getLoadPlanInstance("LOAD_PLAN_NAME")%>' AND TECHNOLOGY = 'ODI'
